EXTRACTED VALUE: "You're not planning on going in, are you?" Faraday said.
"You should have dried it and made him some tea from it to drink. If you don't he'll see ghosts."
He sighed, and smiled ruefully down at me.
"And you haven't given it up. You're still living back then, still dreaming, still the all-American quarterback."
“You said that red-haired poppet’s a friend of your father’s?” he whispered to William. “Find out from him where she’s staying, eh?”
